The paper deals with the problem of finding an optimal statistical model for a given binary string, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of structure functions and automata also suggests a connection to formal languages (cs.FL) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the comparison of deterministic and nondeterministic automata relates to complexity theory (cs.CC).
